@NODE introduction "1. Introduction"
 The ARexx-port is another powerful feature of Wildfire,
 it allows you to:
  -use all features from within other programs
  -enhance the GUI with your own windows
  -write own ARexx-applications which operate like the program itself

 Example: You have designed a nice special effect like
          a transition between three animations or whatever.
          Now you want to integrate this nice feature into
          Wildfire as a "natural feature".
          It's easy ! All you have to do is to design a
          so-called custom-window with buttons, string-gadgets
          switches, ... and to write the procedure itself.

@ENDNODE

@NODE usage "2. Usage"
The port-name is equal to the publicscreen-name
which is visible after clicking into the Wildfire-screen.
For the first running copy of the programm it's "Wildfire",
for the second "Wildfire.1" and so on.
I don't think that's very usefull to run more copies at
one time - but it's possible.

The command-hierarchy is equal to the graphical representation,
this makes it very easy to find the right name of the requested
command. Every command consists of the hierarchy-identifier and
the function-name, e.g. the "Play"-button of the Player-window
is named "P_PLAY".

Most of the arguments are strings or integer-values. It's recommended
to enclose strings into "'"-characters otherwise they are converted
to uppercase by the ARexx-system.


There are three ways to invoke ARexx-commands:
 1. scripts
  1a) called as macros from Wildfire pressing one of the function-keys
  1b) started from a shell
 2. direct commands
 3. external programs

Direct commands are nice to try out a special command, e.g., if you
want to check out the "PL_APPENDDIR"-command type:

 rx "address 'Wildfire' pl_appenddir 'data:grafix/frames'


@ENDNODE

@NODE cwindows "4. Custom-windows"
 Custom-windows are another powerful feature of Wildfire.
 You can create a much own windows as you want, they can
 be loaded, saved, opened, closed, deleted, ... at any time.
 So it's possible to create Toolmanager-like docks on the
 Wildfire-screen which can be loaded at startup.

 But the main purpose is to give you the possibility to enhance
 the program and to fit to your needs.

4.1 Window-elements
-------------------------------------------------------------------
 Custom windows can contain
  -buttons
  -string-gadgets
  -switches
  -lines
  -boxes and
  -texts.
 All these elements remain to the window as long as you
 don't kill them.
 But you have the possibility to apply graphical elements
 which are not stored as structures to the window.
 So you could create an own progress-bar or a function-plotter..

4.2 Window-coordinates
-------------------------------------------------------------------
 Because Wildfire has a fontsensitve GUI you can't use
 absolute coordinates to specify window-elements.
 So you have to design your windows using a topaz.8-font
 to ensure that they look perfect for example with a times.24-font.

 If you want to design a very difficult window with 500
 gadgets, 300 bevelboxes, ... it's seems to be no bad idea
 to use GadToolsBoxą. Using this nice program you can drag and
 size your gadgets in an easy way - just take down the coordinates
 after finishing it.

4.3. A complex example
-------------------------------------------------------------------

 The following example called "Transition.rexx" fades one YAFA-animation
 into another. (This is a very nice feature I currently needed.)
 But it's no trivial ARexx-script like the other supplied macros -
 it creates it's own window with Buttons, Filerequester-gadgets, ... !

 1. Program-structure

    (i) create the window, initialize the parameters
    (ii) perform an endless loop receiving messages:
          1. check for pressed gadgets-> start filerequester etc.
          2. check if the closegadget was pressed -> exit
          3. check if the start-button was pressed -> check the parameters -> do it

 2. Program

    /* are we right ? */
     if ~show('P','Wildfire') then do
      say " Error: The Wildfire-program must be started before executing this script."
      exit
     end

    address 'Wildfire'
     options results

    /* init the globals */
     wnd="Transition"
     tmpdir="shit:"
     frames="30"
     depth="6"

    /* use the default drawers to make life easier */
     t_getanimdrawer
    src1fn=result
    src2fn=src1fn
    destfn=src1fn

    t_getprojectdrawer
    prjfn=result
    doprj="0"

    /* create the window */
    cw_add wnd 476 184
    cw_addgadget wnd string 73 53 291 "Src1"
    cw_addgadget wnd string 73 68 291 "Src2"
    cw_addgadget wnd string 73 85 291 "Dest"
    cw_addgadget wnd string 73 102 291 "Prj"
    cw_addgadget wnd string 155 119 74 "Frames"
    cw_addgadget wnd switch 367 119 74 "CreateProject"
    cw_addgadget wnd string 155 134 74 "Depth"
    cw_addgadget wnd string 367 135 74 "tmpDir"
    cw_addgadget wnd button 30 156 412 "Start"
    cw_addgadget wnd button 367 53 74 "s1Browse"
    cw_addgadget wnd button 367 68 74 "s2Browse"
    cw_addgadget wnd button 367 85 74 "dBrowse"
    cw_addgadget wnd button 367 102 74 "pBrowse"
    cw_addtext wnd 40 14 2 "Note: This window was created during runtime"
    cw_addtext wnd 80 24 2 "and is a functional example demonstrating"
    cw_addtext wnd 80 34 2 "the power of the Wildfire-ARexx-port."
    cw_open wnd
    /* fill the gadgets with some presets */
    cw_setgadget wnd "CreateProject" doprj
    cw_setgadget wnd "Src1" src1fn
    cw_setgadget wnd "Src2" src2fn
    cw_setgadget wnd "Dest" destfn
    cw_setgadget wnd "Prj" prjfn
    cw_setgadget wnd "Frames" frames
    cw_setgadget wnd "Depth" depth
    cw_setgadget wnd "tmpDir" tmpdir

    /* main loop */
    do i=1 to 2
     /* endless-loop (I don't know another way in ARexx) */
     i=i-1
     /* check if the window is open */
     cw_isopen wnd
     qt=result
     if qt=0 then call cleanup /* window was closed -> exit */
     /* wait for gadgets */
     cw_wait wnd
     gadget=result
     /* which gadget was pressed ? */
     if gadget="Src1" then do
      cw_getgadget wnd "Src1"
      src1fn=result
     end
     else if gadget="Src2" then do
      cw_getgadget wnd "Src2"
      src2fn=result
     end
     else if gadget="Dest" then do
      cw_getgadget wnd "Dest"
      destfn=result
     end
     else if gadget="Prj" then do
      cw_getgadget wnd "Prj"
      prjfn=result
     end
     else if gadget="tmpDir" then do
      cw_getgadget wnd "tmpDir"
      tmpdir=result
     end
     else if gadget="s1Browse" then do
      t_getfile src1fn
      src1fn=result
      cw_setgadget wnd "Src1" src1fn
     end
     else if gadget="s2Browse" then do
      t_getfile src2fn
      src2fn=result
      cw_setgadget wnd "Src2" src2fn
     end
     else if gadget="dBrowse" then do
      t_getfile destfn
      destfn=result
      cw_setgadget wnd "Dest" destfn
     end
     else if gadget="pBrowse" then do
      t_getfile prjfn
      prjfn=result
      cw_setgadget wnd "Prj" prjfn
     end
     else if gadget="Frames" then do
      cw_getgadget wnd "Frames"
      frames=result
     end
     else if gadget="Depth" then do
      cw_getgadget wnd "Depth"
      depth=result
     end
     else if gadget="CreateProject" then do
      cw_getgadget wnd "CreateProject"
      doprj=result
     end
     /* let's do it */
     else if gadget="Start" then do
      /* analyze the selected anims */
      t_animinfo src1fn
      err=result
      if err="1" then call error
      else do
       t_getwidth
       width1=result
       t_getheight
       height1=result
       t_getframes
       frames1=result
       t_animinfo src2fn
       err=result
       if err="1" then call error
       else do
        t_getwidth
        width2=result
        t_getheight
        height2=result
        t_getframes
        frames2=result
        /* check the width, ... */
        if frames>=frames1 then call error
        else do
         if frames>=frames2 then call error
         else do
          if width1!=width2 then call error
          else do
           if height1!=height2 then call error
            /* o.k., lets do it */
            /* create the required frames from the 1st animation*/
            c_processor disabled
            m_openconverter
            c_inputtype "YAFAANIM"
            c_inputfilename src1fn
            c_outputtype "PICTURES"
            c_openoutputoptions
            address command "makedir " || tmpdir || "tra"
            address command "makedir " || tmpdir || "trb"
            po_basename tmpdir || "tra/pic"
            po_firstframe frames1-frames+1
            po_lastframe frames1
            po_shift "-" || frames1-frames
            c_convert
            /* create the required frames from the 2nd animation*/
            c_inputfilename src2fn
            po_basename tmpdir || "trb/pic"
            po_firstframe 1
            po_lastframe frames
            po_shift 0
            c_convert
            /* create the picture-list */
            c_closeoutputoptions
            c_inputtype "PICTURES"
            c_outputtype "YAFAANIM"
            c_openinputoptions
            pl_removerange
            pl_appenddir tmpdir || "tra"
            c_closeinputoptions
            /* set the YAFA-parameters */
            c_openoutputoptions
            c_outputfilename destfn
            yo_openanalysis
            a_frames 12
            a_test
            a_use
            c_closeoutputoptions
            /* add the process */
            c_processor enabled
            m_openprocessor
            pc_clear
            pc_depth depth
            pc_openvariables
            v_clear
            v_add "amount"
            pc_closevariables
            pc_add "COMPOSE" 0 0 "amount" tmpdir || "trb/pic" frames FRONT STREAM
            /* create the envelope */
            v_envelope
            ev_move 1 "0.0"
            ev_add frames "100.0"
            ev_viewall
            ev_add frames/3 "25.0"
            ev_add 2*frames/3 "75.0"
            ev_use
            v_envelope /* just to show it */
            /* YEAH !!! */
            c_convert
            address command "delete >NIL: " || tmpdir || "tra all"
            address command "delete >NIL: " || tmpdir || "trb all"
            c_outputexport
            pc_quitadpro
            v_clear
            pc_clear
            m_closeconverter
            m_closeprocessor
            m_openplayer
           end
          end
         end
        end
       end
      end
     end
    end /* main-loop */

    cleanup:
    cw_kill wnd
    exit

    error:
    m_request "An error has occured, please check your parameters."
    return


ą GadToolsBox is Copyright © 1991-93 Jaba Development

@ENDNODE


@NODE errors "3. Error-Messages"
There are 4 error-messages which will be shown together
with the command in the default CON:-window:
 1: wrong number of arguments
 2: wrong arguments
 3: unknown command
 4: command failed

Most of the commands are valid everywhere, but there are exeptions,
e.g. if you haven't defined any variable you can't open
the envelope-window. This would cause error 4.

Normally you can access all program functions without opening
any of the windows, but there are the following exceptions:
 -Timecodes-, AnimInfo-, Envelope- and EnvelopeAdvanced-commands
  require that the corresponding Window was opened
  (This is due the internal data-structure and no error or
   similar.)


If the program executes an ARexx-command all requesters
except the one invoked by the "M_MESSAGE"-command are
turned off, but the requester-messages are shown in the
default CON:-window.

@ENDNODE

@NODE commands "5. Commands"
The command-list below shows all available commands,
values enclosed into brackes are alternative keywords.

 Main:
  M_EXIT			-exit the program
  M_WAIT secs                	-cause the program to wait, useful in
                                 demo-scripts
  M_MESSAGE text               	-display a message in a Wildfire-requester
  M_REQUEST text        	-display a requester, returns 0 if the "O.k."-
				 button was pressed
  M_OPENCONVERTER               -open the converter-window
  M_CLOSECONVERTER            	-close the converter-window
  M_OPENPROCESSOR
  M_CLOSEPROCESSOR
  M_OPENEDITOR
  M_CLOSEEDITOR
  M_OPENPLAYER
  M_CLOSEPLAYER
  M_OPENPREFS
  M_CLOSEPREFS
  M_OPENINFO
  M_CLOSEINFO
  M_MOVE x y			-move the main-window to the location (x,y)
  M_TOFRONT			-turn the Wildfire-screen into foreground
  M_TOBACK			-turn the Wildfire-scrrren into background

Tools:
  T_DELPICTURELIST		-delete the current picturelist and the all
				 the pictures
  T_GETNUMBER title [preset]    -pop up a number-requester, the result can be
                                 received by the calling ARexx-script
  T_GETSTRING title [preset]    -pop up a string-requester
  T_GETFILE title [preset]	-open a filerequester
  T_GETDRAWER titlee [preset]	-open a drawer-requester
  T_ANIMINFO name 		-analyze a YAFA-file, returns 0 if no error
                                 occured. The values of interest like width,
 				 height, ... can be received by using the
                 		 T_GET*-commands
  T_PICINFO name (0=o.k.)       -the same as T_ANIMINFO for ILBM-pictures
  T_GETWIDTH                    -write the width-value obtained by T_ANIMINFO
				 or T_PICINFO to the ARexx-results-stack
  T_GETHEIGHT
  T_GETDEPTH
  T_GETCOLORS
  T_GETFRAMES
  T_GETANIMDRAWER        	-returns the default animation-drawer,
                                 this value could be used as preset
				 for a filerequester
  T_GETPROJECTDRAWER
  T_GETPICDRAWER
  T_GETMODDRAWER
  T_PEXTENSION

 Prefs:
  PR_PLAYERSCREEN name          -change the name of the public-screen used 
				 by the player in window-mode
  PR_SCREENMODE id width height depth -change the settings of the Wildfire-screen
  PR_SCREENDEPTH depth		-change only the depth of the Wildfire-screen
  PR_LOADPREFS
  PR_SAVEPREFS
  PR_OPENPATHS			-open the Paths-window
  PR_CLOSEPATHS
  PR_OPENMACROS
  PR_CLOSEMACROS
  PR_DCLICKTIME val
  PR_STATISTICS (ON|OFF)
  PR_VISUALSUBDIV (5|10|15|20)
  PR_EXPERTMODE (ON|OFF)
  PR_BRUTALBLIT (ON|OFF)
  PR_SESSIONFREQ (ON|OFF)
  PR_NOCHIPMEM (ON|OFF)
  PR_MOVE x y           	-move the prefs-window

 Paths:
  PT_ANIMATIONDRAWER name
  PT_PICTUREDRAWER name
  PT_PROJECTDRAWER name
  PT_SOUNDDRAWER name
  PT_ANNOTATIONDRAWER name
  PT_SESSIONDRAWER name
  PT_PROCESSDRAWER name
  PT_VARIABLESDRAWER name
  PT_ENVELOPEDRAWER name
  PT_MACRODRAWER name
  PT_WINDOWDRAWER name
  PT_HELPDRAWER name
  PT_YAFAPATTERN name
  PT_ANIMPATTERN name
  PT_PROJECTPATTERN name
  PT_PROCESSPATTERN name
  PT_SESSIONPATTERN name
  PT_VARIABLESPATTERN name
  PT_ENVELOPEPATTERN name
  PT_MACROPATTERN name
  PT_WINDOWPATTERN name
  PT_YAFAPLAYER name
  PT_ANIMPLAYER name
  PT_VIEWER name
  PT_ADPRO name
  PT_MOVE x y            	-move the paths-window

 Info:
  I_FREEMEM			-free all lists etc.
  I_MOVE x y                    -move the info-window

 Text:
  TXT_TEXT file			-read the text file "file" and display it's
				 content in the text-window
  TXT_TEXTNC file		-open a text-window with cannot be closed
				 by te user
  TXT_MOVE x y			-move the text-window
  TXT_CLOSE			-close the text-window
  TXT_WAIT			-wait until the user pressed one close-gadget
				 of the text-window
  TXT_CENTRE			-centre the text-window on the Wildfire-screen
 				 and bring it to front

 Player:
